      "content": "so r u saying that saving people from being killed is basically a \"blunder\" if the politics afterward get messy? it feels like u are weighing the long-term political fallout as more important than the actual lives saved in the moment. is there a better way to measure a foreign policy mission than just looking at whether it caused chaos later?",
